				<td colspan="2"><span>2.7? bite me.
<br />

<br />
So in comparison to 2.5 Time mods we will get about +10 ae resists, maybe 8 ds, some irrelevant singing mods (hit cap already anyway....~+320 resists like I have now or ~+340 feh)
<br />

<br />
FT2 on weapon? ok I will stop laughing sometime soon really - I have FT augs banked and I wear more than I can use now.
<br />

<br />
Yes Dmg/Delay, hp, all other stats very nice. So will be all of the other Anguish weapons and they will be considerably easier to obtain.
<br />

<br />
GoD molds offer worn mods from 2.7 (brass) to 2.4 (string).
<br />

<br />
Time and effort required, not only by the bard, but by the dozens of people that must assist them does not work out for me. Once I am in Anguish, and regularly killing the required mobs, I might start working on this...but I kinda doubt I will ever complete it.
<br />

<br />
2.9 would have been my magic number....might be silly to say no over 0.2, but im not gonna harrass folks to help me with this untilI have a much better idea of the itemization in Anguish and GoD.  I suspect that this item will in no way come to hold the all important must haveness of Epic 1.0 as we will have many other options to achieve our mods.
<br />

<br />
Oh and will want to see parses that show the clik is a noticable buff...the 1.5 click has no parseable effect according to many posts I have read. </span></td>
