			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Dissapointed<a name="71024"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 14 04 3:57 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Its my personal opinion that the OoW expansion is attempting to nerf upgrades to bards as a whole. While our new armors are nice, our songs lines are riddled with downgrades. 
<br />

<br />
For example...
<br />

<br />
AE dots don't work if a mob is moving at all... so if it flees, it doesn't die unless you chase it. Thats a genuine nerf, but /rude SoE for making the line pointless now. No AE kiting for j00!
<br />

<br />
Our new and improved snare is a complete and utter waste of a rune. As far as I can tell it lasts 3 ticks, but has no slow component, and its resisted a LOT. Just use the old one or get a Toetwister. A level 68 spell? seriously...
<br />

<br />
Our new charm can only be cast within melee range of intended targets. No swarm kiting for j00!
<br />

<br />
Our new pacify doesn't pacify. The old pacify would lull mobs so that you could walk past them without aggro. This song merely prevents chain aggro from surrounding mobs... and the casting range is the same.
<br />

<br />
Even our DoT's don't land as much in PvP as the Tuyen's set.
<br />

<br />
And to top it off, we get song mods on an epic weapon that are obselete to anyone weilding it.
<br />
Its a great weapon and has an amazing ratio and super stats, but yea... 2.7 mod... come on.
<br />

<br />
The bottom line is that SoE has probably felt that bards are overpowered, but to nerf bards yet again would send many of us scrambling over one another to get to WoW or some other MMORPG.
<br />
However, the diabolical think-tank at SoE masterminded a scheme that would fix our unbalanced asses once and for all! And without the implementation of a nerf or any other spongy substance!
<br />
During OoW development, bards level 66-70 fell off the top of the nerf tree and hit every branch on the way down. We got nerfed by a bunch of suits chattering across a mahogany conference table before any of us had a chance to hit 66. And at 65, we were blissfully unaware of what was happening to our beloved class.
<br />

<br />
-You're not nerfed! How can you call yourself nerfed? All your new stuff is &quot;upgrades&quot; from the old version... sure you can't lull... but your old spell doesn't work on level 70 mobs! See? Upgrade!
<br />
-O yea? Thanks Sony. /rude
<br />

<br />
Still a class very much worth playing... but... its pretty disappointing. I was excited to get new spells and upgrades... man... I was gonna swarm in Fire... all I can do now is shake my head.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
