				<td colspan="2"><span>Just to play devils advocate here:
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">AE dots don't work if a mob is moving at all... so if it flees, it doesn't die unless you chase it. Thats a genuine nerf, but /rude SoE for making the line pointless now. No AE kiting for j00!</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Our AEs were nerfed before the release of Omens, and they gave us quite a few reasons for it, all of which we've discussed a hundred times on these very forums, so I won't go into that one any further.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Our new and improved snare is a complete and utter waste of a rune. As far as I can tell it lasts 3 ticks, but has no slow component, and its resisted a LOT. Just use the old one or get a Toetwister. A level 68 spell? seriously... </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
A lot of bards were actually asking for a song that would only snare, with the idea that we would be able to snare a mob that isn't slowable (since our snare/slow songs won't stick on them). I haven't had a chance to test this song yet, but having a CHANCE to snare it is better then the song not being able to land at all...
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Our new charm can only be cast within melee range of intended targets. No swarm kiting for j00! </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
That's because they didn't want us swarming level 70 mobs. If they wanted us to swarm with this song, they would of made the level limit MUCH lower, like 59 or 60 probably. MANY MANY bards requested a charm that could be used as an additional CC tactic/burst DPS, like we had in the 40s-early 50's. This was a pretty reasonable solution.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Our new pacify doesn't pacify. The old pacify would lull mobs so that you could walk past them without aggro. This song merely prevents chain aggro from surrounding mobs... and the casting range is the same. </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
All classes that could lull or pacify got hit with this one. SOE said it was so people didn't bypass content, primarily in dungeons. I think it's reasonable. If they wanted you to only hit the named mobs in a dungeon, they would've just put them at the zonein. 
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Even our DoT's don't land as much in PvP as the Tuyen's set</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I can't comment on that one, as I don't ever PvP.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">And to top it off, we get song mods on an epic weapon that are obselete to anyone weilding it. 
<br />
Its a great weapon and has an amazing ratio and super stats, but yea... 2.7 mod... come on.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
That one... I don't know. The mod overall is kind of crappy for the difficulty of the quest, yes, but you are getting that mod on all instrument types. It means you can swap out those one or two pieces of gear with a worn mod on it, that you were wearing JUST because it had a worn mod on it, for something much better in that slot. I'm not anywhere near getting 1.5 or 2.0 though, so I can't speak from firsthand knowledge on that.</span></td>
