			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Dissapointed<a name="71029"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 14 04 5:55 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>My point was really that many of the defining features of what once was known as a bard no longer apply post 65.
<br />

<br />
You get to kite one mob at a time now... grats. And it has 50k hp so its going to take you about 10 minutes of running in circles twisting your a$ off to kill it (ain't it fun playing a bard!?). I get that they didn't want people swarm kiting level 70 mobs... but they could've given us a charm upgrade that would still allow us to kite some areas (in addition to the one that MANY MANY bards requested for burst DPS). Maybe instead of that sorry-excuse-for-a snare, we get to charm level 60 mobs. Frankly I think the MANY MANY that were requesting the new charm were just requesting it with the intention to swarm kite in higher level areas. A bard charming a mob in WoS/MPG/RS to use for DPS in combat is a fine way to get yourself killed (they love-tap for 600+), but I don't know if it has a practical use beyond that.
<br />

<br />
As for the lulling nerf... in most of the top end exp zones there aren't many mobs that see invis. But there are mobs in areas like MPG/WoS/RS that will be &quot;unaffected&quot; by any lull, so you have to get crafty on pulls anyway. And even if you could lull the mobs surrounding the &quot;unaffected&quot; one, you'd get pummelled when it wore off, so there's really no way to bypass that content. You can't lull through much of the old content anyway... BoT maybe. Was that really such a problem? I tried it in a lot of groups until I realized, we were a lot better off just killing things instead of wiping our group.
<br />

<br />
As for the new snare, its not worth the spell slot it takes up. I have yet to encounter a mob that I would use it on... maybe in Anguish, as I haven't been there yet. Riftseekers in an exp group perhaps? But I doubt it because I can slow many of those. A better alternative would have been to make it a level 55 spell that you could buy from a vendor. Or maybe do a little quest or something for it. Muramite runes sell for 30k+ on my server. This spell isn't worth anything close to that. Weak excuse for a level 68 spell imo.
<br />

<br />
As for the AE nerf... old news, yes. But I'm still pissed about it. Particularly because I have to farm old content to skillup Blacksmithing and Tailoring. What I usually do is round up a buttload of mobs (say, Sonic Wolves in Hollowshade moor... cause you need 1000+ of their &quot;shrieking substances&quot; to max smithing). So say I have like 40 mobs... I'm AEing... AEing... then all of the sudden half of them take off. Well, guess what. As long as they're running my AE doesn't do dick. So they escape and survive and I've wasted my effort, and it takes twice as long to farm the 1000 shrieking substances, 1000 wailing substances, and 2000 swirling shadows I need for the combines to max the skill. Hours are added to the time-sink and subtracted from my life if I want skillups. I guess that pisses me off a little. 
<br />
By the way... these mobs run at like 40%, so AE snaring them doesn't help.
<br />

<br />
There are ways to remedy what SoE has determined to be a problem. But instead of getting creative with the mob content, they got creative with you and me. Thereby biting the hand that feeds them.
<br />

<br />
As of right now, the population on my server has become so delapidated that the top guild on my server cannot attempt end-game content. Thats because people are leaving. Moving to greener pastures like WoW, or even just quitting altogether.
<br />
As a result, 90% of the power gamers on Tallon and Vallon have requested a server merger so that we can rejuvinate our population and tackle this content.
<br />
SoE was kind enough to set up a serverwide meeting in-game which about 400 or so people attended. We want this to happen. The PvP community will die if it doesn't. Power guilds on Tallon are starting to become one guild. Its pretty serious.
<br />

<br />
Altering my capeabilities and creating more ridiculously long quests do not make EQ more fun. Thats why people leave. 
<br />
Sure, OoW has some neat new stuff. But its like, equipment has higher stats, mobs hit for a ton... etc., etc.
<br />
Its kind of like more of the same, except its not the same. Now you can't swarm or AE kite. You are more limited in your abilities now...
<br />
Come on SoE... lets get a little more creative here...
<br />

<br />
here's a new idea since you guys seem to be stuck in the same creative rat-hole you've been in since velious...
<br />

<br />
How about an epic battle between 2 Gods... They hit each other for a ton... and one will definitely die. You're assisting one God and if the NPC gets the KS, you don't get loot. If the good guy loses, the bad guy turns on your raid and you either kill him and get loot, or you wipe.
<br />

<br />
Take that to the board-room, mfers.
<br />

<br />
And how about like... a Tomb Raider style timed single PC maze with like 8 unique instances - not mappable. If you run into a monster you either kill it or keep going and it chases you. As time lapses, lava comes out of holes in the floor behind you... traps dispell buffs... its absolute chaos... but the rewards may be worth it...
<br />

<br />
You can even add like a first person shooter element to new instances.
<br />

<br />
Sorry. I've gotten myself off on a tangent. I'll copy this to the appropriate forums on EQlive...</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
