<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=32705">Bloodband of Malice</a> Percussion 2.7, finger
<br />
or
<br />
<a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=30274">Rapier of Somber Notes</a> Percussion 2.9, weapon
<br />

<br />
There's a 2.8 Singing mod weapon from Texvu, which isn't listed on alla's for some reason.  It's listed in my magelo dreamlist though, the edge of chaos.  (there's a ranger in my guild that has it)  There's also other items with a 2.6 singing mod. 
<br />

<br />
The best string on Alla's is a 2.6 sleeve from MPG trials. 
<br />

<br />
Alla's also doesn't list the ring from Tacvi, Ring of Organic Darkness, which is a 2.7 mod. 
<br />

<br />
So, yeah, you can have the 2.7 mod (or very close to it) from a suit of worn equipment or weapons, there's no need for it on the epic if there's other better DPS weapons that you can be using from that zone. 
<br />

<br />
So, IMO, to bring it in line with the other epic 2.0 make it a 36/22 and leave the 2 magic damage on it, and make the mod 2.9 or 3.0, basically, something better enough that we'd use it over anything else available to us, while simultaneously allowing us a bit more leeway for itemization. </span></td>
