<br />
To put this weapon more in like with anguish quality loot, need to bump the ratio and mod for a start. Really the epic 2.0's ratio is way too low. Look at what ranger's epic is. Thiers is a 42/24. The simple fact is if a ranger and abard are wielding the same exact weapon, rangers will do more dps. Why give us a weapon that has a worse ratio? We should get a weapon with a ratio in line with thiers, and thier high dmg table from being a dps class will make up the difference. Really need a bump from 34(+2)/22 to 37(+2)/22. Maybe even 38(+2)/22 would be fair. The magic damage alone would allow for a higher ratio in weapon but also giving us a more random effect to low the over all dps of the weapon (ie: a 40/22 is always going to out perform a 38(+2)/22). Secondly the mod. Most bards by this point in the game will have 2.7 or better on thier gear. This is supposed to be an EPIC weapon, something we wield and use and is hard to replace... why give us an inferior mod on it compared to our other gear? Give us a 2.9 mod, that will be in line with what we are wearing... I've yet to see 3.0 worn mods, and 2.9 would certainly be equal or an upgrade to what we have so we actually wield our epic *gasp*. Third, find a new click or make it like 15% so our parses actually show some data indicating that the click is running. Its really a joke when you have to use markers in a parse to determine if the effect is on or off.
