				<td colspan="2"><span>Several problems Ive moticed.
<br />

<br />
The argument that their is better worn gear out there.  Yah there is.  But its not in one tidy package.  I've been in an EP guild for 6 months, and I still do not have all 5 instrument/singing mods (equal to or better than epic 1).  And honestly, the only reason I'm trying to is to bank epic 1.0, so i can get something with a better ratio.  Excluding mods found on BP's (Rarity issues, hence better mods), how many pieces of gear and from what zone levels would it take to get 2.7 mods?  It will take a long time to bank 2.0 because you have 5 pieces of better gear.
<br />

<br />
Our ratio.  Epic 1 (16/26), Epic 1.5 (24/22).  Epic 2 (34/22).  As a piercer, our ratio should never be better than our rogue brethren.  Technically, if we are a hybrid of anything, it is of rogues.  Do beastlords get better ratios than monks?  Also, all our epics are designed around the idea that its an &quot;Off Hand Wep.&quot;  Its old faithful.  It sits in the offhand and stays their.  How many times did you see Epic 1 in someones primary hand?  Prolly not many, and you know why, because its ratio sucked, but it was amazingly useful so we kept it in secondary.
<br />

<br />
The clicky, I don't particulary care for.  Mainly for the reason it doesn't really help the bard himself much.  Dance of the Blade helped us, AND helped our group.  This clicky, just helps the group.  Something like a 1 min Chorus song that added mana to US and our groups would have worked better than this.
<br />

<br />
As for the other combat effects, its all part of the balancing game.  We get FT2 because everyother mana user got it.  We get a combat resist because every other class got one, and they determined Stun Resist was the best choice.
