				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Dissapointed<a name="71492"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 24 04 6:47 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Yes, we are a unique class.  However all of our gear is designed around the following.
<br />

<br />
We duel weild weapons, just like rogues, warriors, and rangers (weapon list on Ifir, GBoK, and 99% of our weaps).  Our ratios are tied to those numbers.  We do not use 2 handers, and dont get the enhanced ratios that that Knights get because they are limited to them.  Knights get better 1 handers because they dont get to duel weild at all.
<br />

<br />
For armor, we are aplate class, and treated as such.
<br />

<br />
For other miscellaneous gear, we are considered hybrids.  Rangers, Knights, Beastlords and us.  Disagree all you want, but when the Abalone Engraved Mask is a Hybrid Mask, we are a Hybrid.  Other pieces of equipement come to mind also.  
<br />

<br />
Argue all you want that it is because we have a mana bar, but like it or not, the DEVLOPERS consider us a HYBRID.  Personally, I think we are Plate class casters (much like clerics), but until you convince the coders otherwise, you have to follow their rules.
<br />

<br />
Did we get screwed with the epic? no.  We got the same ratio that warriors and rangers got (within a slim percent).  We got a weapon that 90% of the folks out there would use gladly, with an instrument mod that effectively gives you 3.5 mod to all (yes, im counting our AA).  Why not 2.8, 30, or even 3.4? because they want us to use our frigging instruments.  Why the h*ll else give them to us?
<br />

<br />
But here's some real math for you.  You need 5 items to bank the new epic, or have gear that makes it obsolete.  Assuming you raid 5 targets a night, and each target drops 2 loots on average, that 10 pieces of gear per night.  40 people on a raid (nice solid number), that means 25% of you receive an upgrade per night.  After 4 nights, roughly everyone gets an upgrade.  So after 20 nights of raiding, you all have 5 pieces of upgraded gear.  Lets assume one of those 5 pieces is an instrument mod with better than 2.7 mod.   Therefore after 100 nights of raiding you have all 5 of your mods, and your new epic is obsolete.   And that assumes optimal conditions.  What happens if 3 of our mods are on Plate armor, which we compete with 4 other classes for? or we have an overage of bards, or the raid leaders dtermine the new bp needs to go to the main tank first?
<br />

<br />
If you think this is a piece of junk, ask kinuvan if he would use, or Medaan if he does?  Before he swapped servers, Xevs top bard carried 1.5 as a wep.  Im willing to bet he would use 2.0 in a heartbeat, and wouldn't complain that he could get better before hand.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Rappa
<br />

<br />
